section.section:
Within 30 days of the insurer appointing an insurance producer, the insurer shall include the following information in the insurer's producer register:
the insurance producer's name;
the license number assigned to the insurance producer by the Commissioner;
the date that the insurer appointed the insurance producer; and
any additional information that the Commissioner may require.

This subsection applies to:
an insurer;
an authorized representative of an insurer;
an insurance producer;
the Commissioner; and
an organization of which the Commissioner is a member that compiles information required under this section and makes it available to other insurance commissioners or regulatory or law enforcement agencies.

Any document, material, or other information that is subject to this subsection is:
confidential and privileged;
not subject to Title 10, Subtitle 6 of the State Government Article;
not subject to subpoena; and
not subject to discovery or admissible in evidence in any private civil action.
